Products.RichDescription: Much of the skin will stay green when ripe. A ripe fresh mango should have a fragrant tropical fruity aroma a full colour and will give slightly to the touch. Mangoes should not be refrigerated until they are ripe. Fully ripe mangoes can be stored in the fridge for a few days. Never store mangoes in plastic bags. Cut from the stem end along the stone. Score the flesh of the cheek into a diamond pattern. Turn inside out. Eat the flesh straight from the cheek or cut off the cubes.

Products.RichDescription:
Butternut Pumpkin

Though they are called Pumpkin in Australia or New Zealand, the Butternut is actually a type of Squash and more closely related to Cucumbers or Melons than Pumpkins.

They have a distinct nutty, dense and sweet taste similar to Pumpkins, which makes them great for soups. They also hold their shape really well, which makes them a great addition to roasted veggie salads and are perfect for baking too
